Last weekend, Oshwal Auditorium in Nairobi played host to the latest production starring Siddharth Randeria, Rang Rangila Gujjubhai.Randeria is an Indian actor of Gujarati theatre and films. The play was well-attended and critically acclaimed for its comedy and entertainment.Past productions staged at Oshwal Auditorium include Rumours, It Runs in the Family, Jack &amp; the Beanstalk, Karibu Simba, Joseph and His Technicolour Dreamcoat, Alladin and The Jungle Book.The Oshwal Academy Auditorium is located on the Oshwal Academy-Junior High campus situated on the corner of 1st Parklands Avenue and Mpaka Road.Opened in 1999, the theatre has hosted many local and international productions over the years.